China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while unveiling an anti-secession law.
MAC Deputy Chairman Chiu Tai-shan criticized Beijing's move, warning of a legal basis for military action against Taiwan.
President Chen Shui-bian condemned the law as a threat to stability.
The US and EU also oppose the legislation.
Mainland Affairs Council Chairman Joseph Wu warned of a referendum if Taiwan is forced to accept Beijing's terms.
Pro-independence activists urge a strong response.
The Legislative Yuan plans to pass a resolution against the law.
China insists the law aims to prevent Taiwan independence.
